cs.FL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.PL

The paper deals with the Parikh finite word automaton (PA) and its variants, which are models of computation for regular languages. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also discusses the expressiveness and decidability properties of these models, which are topics related to logic and complexity theory. Hence, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper uses techniques such as pumping-style lemmas and identifies an explicit language recognized by no deterministic PA, which are related to the theory of data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the properties of affine transformations, which are related to programming languages and semantics, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) a possible category as well.
